<title>GERMANY: Audi, VW to split cost of Brazilian plant.</title>
<headline>Audi, VW to split cost of Brazilian plant.</headline>
<dateline>INGOLSTADT, Germany 1996-12-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>German carmaker Audi AG, the luxury wing of Volkswagen AG, said on Tuesday that it would split a 750 million mark ($481.9 million) investment in a planned production plant in Brazil 50/50 with the parent company.</p>
<p>It added that the new plant would start production of the A3, its new small car, by 1998. VW would also produce its Vento model at the plant, Audi said.  </p>
<p>Last week, Audi said total investment in the proposed Brazilian production facility could exceed 500 million marks. The plant will produce vehicles for Latin American markets.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525</p>
<p>($ = 1.556 German Marks)</p>
